data.text: @Gamera_Man @brandonhicks @dunekacke Our cases have been going down for the last 2 weeks or so but the death counts are hovering around the same numbers. I was wondering if I missed something.
@abcrawford83 @brandonhicks @dunekacke Death counts lag case counts by a week or so.
@brandonhicks @dunekacke Why are our death counts so high? Usually when the case counts start dropping significantly the death counts drop too.
@brandonhicks @brandonhicks thank you for continuing your efforts ❤️

@brandonhicks Test at home... no one reporting ...
Of course numbers go down 🙄
@brandonhicks Are we seeing Omicron more slowly progressing to death? It seems deaths have remained up for while. Long after decreased cases and even decreased hospitalizations, right??
@brandonhicks Transmission/new cases has fallen rapidly, unfortunately the deaths have not . . . .
@brandonhicks Still to many deaths until there are zero
